@MarcanoFilms @WalkerAmerica Great, then you’re all set for August.

@AsyncN8 @WalkerAmerica I spent over a decade as an engineer (including writing code and overseeing software engineers), and am a partner at one of the largest venture firms in Bitcoin.

So, naturally I monitor all these developments closely and will provide my view if asked.

@AsyncN8 @WalkerAmerica And if you’re interested in further reading, you might also be interested in the technical+economic paper I co-authored on contentious soft forks back in 2024:
https://t.co/SPMwgcb8X9

People have a right to run other implementations (pretty low risk) or build support for a broad-consensus fork (harder), or try to rush a minority-consensus fork (good luck).

This fork still lets the witness be crammed with all sorts non-monetary data, with minimal extra cost. It’s interesting (I do think there’s merit in an op return limit), but currently doesn’t have a lot of support and imo is falsely marketed as being existential.

I’m also interested in certain forks that could enable LN Symmetry or consensus cleanup (but fixing), but it both fortunately and unfortunately is very hard to change bitcoin consensus so they’ve been around for years.

If someone figures out how to materially reduce spam with minimal technical risks, and goes through a review with accumulating technical support, I’m all ears.

@AsyncN8 @WalkerAmerica I keep track of multiple fork proposals I like that have been worked on for years, including ones that would add LN Symmetry or perform consensus cleanup (bug fixes). Happy to add yours to the list to watch.

But if people ask me if this is an existential risk, my answer is no.

